      <description>&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-add-a-paper-to-the-default-library&#34;&gt;Example: add a paper to the default library&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;papis add ~/tmp/Downloads/2103.08123.pdf --from doi https://doi.org/10.1103/PhysRevLett.128.040403 --folder-name quantumn_mechanics/Ruling_Out_Real-Valued_Standard_Formalism_of_Quantum_Theory&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you download PDF papers from journel website such as PRL, you don&amp;rsquo;t need to specify doi when adding the paper, because it is already included in the paper file.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;ref&#34;&gt;Ref&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://papis.readthedocs.io/en/latest/?badge=latest&#34;&gt;papis docs&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
